                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-08-07 - Summary of Gorden Posts (Long)</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> Gorden has been busy: Here is a summary of posts over the last day or two:
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001899.html"><b>Abashi
    has Call of Bones Changed?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Abashi has Call of Bones
    changed? Most sites list it as doing 16mana for 16hp per tick yet recent
    discussions seem to indicate the spell is only 8mana for 8hp.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    No, the spell hasnt changed. The spoiler sites that parse the spdat.eff just
    dont get the full picture from that file.<br>
    <br>
  </li>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001935.html"><b>Abashi
    - FD has changed on test</b></a><br>
    I havent seen a first-hand accounting of any change to feign death on test
    at this point. Every post has been from someone who knows someone on test
    who plays a monk, or by someone on test who knows someone who plays a monk.<br>
    <br>
    No intentional change has been made, and I havent see anything to indicate
    that any unintentional change was made. I took a look at it myself, and it
    appears that its operating the same as it has for months.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001938.html"><b>How
    is it a Mage with the ac of 250, and a Shadow Knight with the ac of 450 both
    take</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: How is it a Mage with
    the ac of 250, and a Shadow Knight with the ac of 450 both take the same
    amout of damage from a mob. I have a level 22 Shadow Knight and a level 22
    Cleric. When I was fighting DW Crocs they both would get hit for 40 points
    of damage. Why is that? If a Shadow Knight has higher ac then why does he
    take the same amout of damage? I have seen this with other classes as well.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Over time, youll find that the highly armored SK will take less damage per
    hit on average than your lightly armored mage.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001979.html"><b>I
    took the risk...so where is the reward?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Okay. I understand the
    concept of Risk v Reward. Simply put, the higher the risk the greater the
    reward. So tell me, where is the reward? Why is the loot dropped from mobs
    not more consistant with the level of the mob? Here is a story for you to
    ponder.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Did you get experience from the encounter?<br>
    Did you have fun doing it?<br>
    <br>
    Ok, so you got a bad roll on loot when killing one creature.
    &quot;Rewards&quot; arent always based on loot.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/002003.html"><b>Please
    add /who all location</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Hello, I know for a fact
    that GMs have this command. So yes it can be done. Now if bandwidth is a
    problem why dont you simply limit the amount you can see so that if there is
    70 people in the zone it would just say 70 people in zone and only show
    maybe 25 30 names? Sound familar yeah its the way all /who all anyhting
    works. No if you just dont wanna give it to us (which makes no sence) then
    thats fine, but how can you say it cant be done? Thank you, Iuvian.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Indeed the GMs have the ability, it just cant be given to the public for
    technical reasons. Bandwidth is only a part of it, the other part being
    server load. There is a relatively small number of people who currently have
    the ability, its just not scalable to the potential of having 60K+ people at
    peak doing it.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/002026.html"><b>Quiver
    in ammo slot (a work around for the code problem)</b></a><br>
    <i><font color="#FF0000">[Quote from original post: Yes I know the quiver
    can not go in the ammo slot due to code reasons - However, stacks of arrows
    can - what if an up to 80 arrow limit was placed in the ammo slot.<br>
    To make stacks over 20 arrows you would use a special four slot quiver with
    a combine button that would take the 20 SAME TYPE arrows in each stack and
    combine them into a mega stack that would go in the ammo slot.<br>
    </font><font color="#072876"><br>
    The arrows would take on a quiver graphic and be placed in the ammo slot and
    have the larger number in the corner.<br>
    <br>
    Make this special quiver cost 10 times the normal quiver because it can
    reduce the number of slots needed to carry arrows.]</font></i><br>
    <br>
    Its a good idea, unfortunately, stacks cannot exceed 20 given game
    architecture, and containers cant be worn in the main inventory slots.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/002100.html"><b>Gees,
    Im sure everyone has experienced disconnect deaths, why then...</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Well, maybe it is
    Verants fault for not protecting me when I am disconnected and letting a mob
    beat the @#%* out of me while I look at a screen telling me what I already
    know.<br>
    The only thing I can hope for is that I am running when I get disconnected.
    Why doesnt Verant exit me from the game when I have NO control over what
    happens in the game?]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Because then people would &quot;pull the plug&quot; to avoid death.<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: They should have some
    way to quickly determing if it was a valid LD death and perform a full exp
    res]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    There isnt a way to determine the difference between someone &quot;pulling
    the plug&quot; and someone whos ISP has a problem. We cant even go off of
    high packet-loss, because its easy to simulate. What we can tell is if a
    problem is on our end, because its not just one person who goes LD, but
    thousands.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/002109.html"><b>Necros
    and Poison</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Ok I am not asking for
    any special Necromancer godlike powers, but if Necros are *masters* of the
    dead, disease, and poison, why is it that we do not get Cure poison? I mean
    we get Cure Disease, and Counteract Disease so why not Cure poison? Several
    of our spells are poisonous in nature meaning we have spent many hours
    dealing with the components. So WHY NOT CURE POISON?]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Actually I believe that Shaman actually have better poison and disease-based
    spells. Anyway, necros get cure disease because rotting corpses and disease
    tend to go hand-in-hand. Their ability to cast poison-based spells doesnt
    mean that they should be able to cure them.<br>
    In any case, I do think that necromancers have more than enough abilities as
    it is, so it really wouldnt be prudent to expand them into this area.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/002110.html"><b>What
    is verant server policy?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Just one thing ; will i
    see new server again or will verant just split now ? ...<br>
    And where such thing are planned if they are ? ..]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Its hard to say. Though we dont currently have a new server planned, its
    probably safe to say that the next server, should one be planned, will most
    likely be a split. It is however hard to tell what will happen past that
    point.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000136.html"><b>Gordon:
    Fatties are getting the shaft in equipment</b></a><br>
    There should be some advantages for those who choose to forego the immense
    advantages that come with choosing to be a large race.<br>
    <br>
  </li>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001076.html"><b>Gordon-
    Vermaculated armor once again</b></a><br>
    This issue has been addressed with the Live Team several times, and the
    outcome is that the stats on these items are intentional. As such, were
    closing the issue.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001224.html"><b>Moss
    Covered Twig</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Can you confirm or deny
    if you are going to nerf this weapon yet?]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    We still havent made a decision regarding these extremely low-delay weapons
    yet. Well be sure to publicize it when the decision has been made.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001231.html"><b>Lore
    Items..</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Supposedly an item with
    the LORE ITEM tag is supposed to have info on it that can be revealed with
    an Identify. But most lore items either dont need a description because it
    is inherent in the title, or are lore simply to prevent a user from having
    more than one at a time (magician summoned staffs come quickly to mind)]</i><br>
    <br>
    </font>I think that were going to begin adding actual &quot;lore&quot; to
    those lore items soon. We have a writer on the EQ Live staff who will
    probably take that up soon.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001239.html"><b>Gordon/Abashi/Verant
    Can this be done?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Let everyone
    &quot;do&quot; a dungeon at the same time.<br>
    <br>
    Give the dungeon a maximum number of players (like a chat room has a maximum
    number of participants)<br>
    <br>
    This should be in multiples of 6 (for groups)<br>
    <br>
    If more players want to enter a dungeon than its maximum, the server creates
    a second copy of the dungeon for the next set of players.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    We actually want to encourage people to spread out in the world and
    experience new things. Spawing multiple copies of dungeons would work
    against this goal. Another issue would be that people might have a hard time
    getting into the same &quot;copy&quot; of the dungeon when they wanted to.
    Finally, we would lose control over the rate at which items enter the game.
    I can see a situation where large guilds would purposely create multiple
    copies for the purposes of camping the same thing in those multiple copies.<br>
    Its not a good solution for a MMOG.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001241.html"><b>Gordon
    Look! :) Mana Regen Again ....</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Ive noticed that it is
    taking FOREVER to med with my skill stuck at 255 (or 252?). We continue to
    get more mana intensive spells and more mana past the level 50 mark, but I
    am stuck with the same med capability I will have at level 60 that I had at
    level 50. So is there a fix proposed for this? How about an item that
    casts... or has the effect of clarity? If you can do the effect of SoW for J
    Boots.... why not clarity for another type of item? Seems only fair since
    the value of SoW is not near what clarity is anymore.]</i><br>
    <br>
    </font>The &quot;solution&quot; for what you are mentioning is grouping with
    classes that have the ability to increase your regen rate. Bards and
    enchanters can do this for you, and can certainly increase it at a rate
    beyond what it was at level 50.<br>
    <br>
    Putting in other ways to increase mana regeneration would unbalance the
    game. The methods available to increase the rate of regeneration do so to
    the greatest extent that weve designed for the game.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001229.html"><b>Too
    many people on a sever? What to do now?</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Do you think there is a
    way to make respawn times faster on full servers?]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Unfortunately, thats not the answer to overcrowding. Lack of things to kill
    in a particular area is one of the things that gets people to spread out to
    some of the other areas in the game. There is now more than enough land and
    things to kill in the game to support well over two thousand people, though
    as we mentioned before, were not raising the official peak-usage target.<br>
    <br>
    The other issue is that dungeons are laid out so that if they are
    &quot;done&quot; (rather than camped), several groups can move through them
    and get enough time to rest. Increasing spawn times, by even a minute,
    upsets that balance and actually promotes camping.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001243.html"><b>The
    easiest way to silence post-50 monk complaints</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Simply put, give us
    triple attack at 60 like the warriors. We will be able to outdamage them
    again by a significant margin. Our lower ac wont be as big an issue because
    groups will want us again for our damage output.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Triple attack is basically just &quot;something neat&quot;. I dont
    understand why this is a frequent point with monks, as it really doesnt fire
    that often for warriors to really swing balance. If monks want it just
    because its a skill that they dont have, thats really not a compelling
    reason to add it.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001244.html"><b>Magicians</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: Can us mages get some
    &quot;fun&quot; spells put into the game? Perhaps find a way to spice up the
    class without unbalancing it?]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    I thought we did some of that with the bundle/pack spells that we threw in.
    They are really there just for fun, as you suggest. If you can think of some
    other &quot;fun&quot; spells, we could throw those in as well<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001246.html"><b>Post
    50 cleric spell order screwed up -- clerics constantly told Verant, and
    still!</b></a><br>
    They were initially correct towards the end of the RoK beta, however at some
    point they got messed up. You are right that a few are out of order, for
    instance, with group heroism coming before group resolution.<br>
    <br>
    Rather than just put them in the right order, which would be considered as a
    nerf by some, were going to just change a spell or two to something more
    appropriate for the level. For instance, I believe that we are changing
    &quot;United Resolve&quot; to a &quot;group symbol&quot; spell that only
    uses one component.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001623-2.html"><b>RUMOR!!
    If its true I will never play EQ again</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: according to people I
    know and things that have been derived from the test server atmosphere Feign
    death has an added recast time to it, so feigns cannot be done in
    succession.]</i><br>
    <br>
    </font>Interestingly enough, that was a suggestion that was made here on the
    boards a while back to eliminate feign-pulling: Make it so that the recycle
    timer doesnt start until you stand up.<br>
    <br>
    In any case, we havent implemented it. I checked out feign quite a bit
    during the last great-feign debate, and also just checked it now, and it
    appears to be the same to me.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001700.html"><b>Abashi
    - Whats the ETA on the Disease line being upgraded?</b></a><br>
    Im not really sure what may have been indicated in the past in regards to
    this line. As of now, the disease line is considered adequate. The extended
    duration of the spells was intentional, and is balanced with the
    environment.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001800.html"><b>The
