    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001807.html"><b>Abashi:
    Casual Player Server? Ideas from a power gamer.</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: How do you know its 20
    hours a week? Please define the source of that datum.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    Its actually over 20 hours per week, much closer to 23. The data is fairly
    easy to come by, as we can tell who is logged into the servers at any given
    time, and how long they are logged in.<br>
    <br>
    <font color="#FF0000"><i>[Quote from original post: That 20 hour figure is
    fine if you reduce the weak to two days. I play about 20 hours a week
    myself, but thats based on the fact that I put in all 20 in one session, and
    then take a long break. Not everybody is as fortunate as me to have a nice
    schedule.]</i><br>
    </font><br>
    I know what you are saying. Thats pretty typical of the average player. The
    average player typically plays a few hours each day with one long session
    once or twice a week.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001814.html"><b>Deleting
    petitions.</b></a><br>
    <i><font color="#FF0000">[Quote from original post: No doubt many people
    including myself have made petitions, only to be able to resolve the
    situation themselves or with help from other players moments later before a
    GM was able to reply.<br>
    Unfortunately once the problem has been solved, the petition is still
    waiting, and the sender has no way of removing the petition from the que, or
    informing the GM`s that they no longer need assistance, which no doubt is a
    waste of theyre time, and players who still need help are left waiting
    longer.<br>
    </font><font color="#072876"><br>
    Is there any chance that a means of deleting petitions sent would be added
    to the game?]</font></i><br>
    <br>
    Thats a good idea. Ill mention it to the team.<br>
    <br>
    Players can currently only file one petition per character. A &quot;delete
    petition&quot; command (e.g. /delpetition) would just inform the server that
    you are no longer in need of help allowing the server to expire the petition</li>
